                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Consulate-General</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1895.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2549.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to previous correspondence
                    relating to the case of Mr. Julio Sanguily, I have now the honor to inform the
                    Department that Mr. Miguel F. Viondi, the lawyer chosen by Mr. Sanguily for his
                    defense, tells me that the judge encharged with the examination proceedings has
                    assured him that the process (sumario) will be sent this week to the trial
                    court.</p>
                <p>Mr. Viondi will then see it and make me a synopsis of it. As soon as it is
                    received I will send a copy of it to the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ramon O. Williams</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Consul-General.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
